On 19 Jun 2016, at 12:24, l.stramaccia wrote:

> Dear colleagues.,
> it is with great sorrow that I inform you that Sibe Mardesic passed =20=

> two days ago in Zagreb, at the age of 90.
> Although Sibe was not a categorist but a general and algebraic =20
> topologist, I am sure that most of you knew his name and possibly =20
> his work dedicated from the early 80=92s to Shape and Strong Shape =20
> Theory. Anyway he was deeply aware of categorical methods as =20
> testified by the large amount of his papers,  the book  <Shape =20
> theory,  North Holland(1982)> with Jack Segal, finishing with the =20
> monumental <Strong shape and homology, Springer  (2000)>. He was =20
> the first to categorize Borsuk=92s Shape theory adopting the =93inverse =
=20
> system=94  approach. Less than one month ago he told me the he was =20
> hardly working on a problem concerning products in the strong shape =20=

> category of topological spaces.
> For all who had the pleasure and the honor tho know him and to work =20=

> with him, Sibe leaves a great legacy of mathematical passion and =20
> rigour together with  a special humanity.
> He his deeply missed by all his friends and colleagues all over the =20=

> world.
> Ciao Sibe, wherever you are now.
> Luciano Stramaccia
